                                                                                                                                                     Meta Data Tags
                                                                                                                                                     
   I - Meaning : Metadata is data about data ( It provides information that describes, explains, or gives context to other data ), meta data tags are often used to provide additional information about a document, web page, or other types of content (  help with SEO (Search Engine Optimization)) . used in <head>.
   
   II - HTML Metadata Tags for Websites : 
      1 - Title : Sets the title of the document == <title> content </title>.
      2 - General Meta Tags : 
          <meta name= "author" content ="Oussama"> ( Author of the page ).
          <meta name= "description" content ="An overview of metadata tags for websites."> ( Page description ).
          <meta name= "keywords" content ="metadata, SEO, HTML, web development"> ( Keywords for search engines ).
	  <meta name= "icon" content="icon/path" type="image,icon..">
      3 - Open Graph Tags (for Social Media Sharing) : 
           <meta property="og:title" content="Metadata Tags Guide">
           <meta property="og:description" content="Learn about different metadata tags for websites.">
           <meta property="og:image" content="https://example.com/image.jpg">
           <meta property="og:url" content="https://example.com/metadata-guide">
           <meta property="og:type" content="website">
      4 - Robot tag : 
           <meta name="robots" content="index, follow"> ( Instructions for search engine crawlers )
